<sentence id="6">Transfection of kinase-deficient mutants of IKKalpha and IKKbeta into either human Jurkat T or 293 cells also inhibits NF-kappaB-dependent reporter gene expression induced by Tax .</sentence>
<sentence id="7">Similarly , a kinase-deficient mutant of NIK ( NF-kappaB-inducing kinase ) , which represents an upstream kinase in the TNF-alpha and IL-1 signaling pathways leading to IKKalpha and IKKbeta activation , blocks Tax induction of NF-kappaB .</sentence>
